                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d470">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/127: Telegram (part air)</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-01-17T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >January 17, 1935—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 19—6:30]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>24. Consulate’s 21, January 16, 10 a.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>The Italians are making every effort to have the Abyssinians withdraw
                        their invocation of the Covenant. Avenol<note n="6" xml:id="d470fn6">Joseph
                            L. A. Avenol, Secretary General of the League of Nations.</note> stated
                        to the Abyssinian delegate that the Italians had informed him that they
                        would regard a bringing of the matter before the Council while direct
                        negotiations were in progress as prejudicial to a friendly
                        settlement.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>The Abyssinians do not consider that the present direct conversations
                        constitute negotiations in any acceptable sense and are standing upon their
                        appeal. In this they are acting under instructions.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
